a. Of or pertaining to system; consisting in system;
methodical; formed with regular connection and adaptation or
subordination of parts to each other, and to the design of the whole;
as, a systematic arrangement of plants or animals; a systematic course
of study.
a. Proceeding according to system, or regular method;
as, a systematic writer; systematic benevolence.
a. Pertaining to the system of the world; cosmical.
